args:
Having rescued Sarisse, the prince and
company are led to a forest refuge where she
and Luca's people are hiding. They decide to
prepare for a confrontation with the Empire by
eradicating fiends the Empire has set free.
As if! Let GO of me!
You there! Unhand her at once!
What manner of savage picks a fight\nwith a frail little girl?
The kind whose bones are about to get\nsnapped in two.
I-it's the traitor and his band of criminals!
Bahhh... Retreat! We need to report this\nto Captain Harle!
I'm fine, but...how do you know my name?
Ho, Sarisse! I'm glad you're safe.\nI was so worried.
Luca? WHAT?! How are you not dead?!
Ha ha! Oh, come on. Do you really think\na dragon could kill the likes of m—
You idiot! That was a DRAGON,\nand you were INSANE to take it on!
Holy carp! I think that blow lifted Luca a\ncouple'a feet off the ground.
I cheerfully retract my previous statement\nabout a ＂frail little girl.＂
Luca? You still with us, buddy?\nOh man, I don't think eyes are supposed\nto roll back in your head like that.
*sniff* It's his fault for worrying me.
You may have to wait until his organs\nshift back into their normal positions.
Well, thanks for rescuing my dumb brother.\nWe've been looking for him day and night.
And that's why you elected to greet me\nwith your fist instead of a wave?
Well, that will teach you to catch a\nlady by surprise.
You should go easy on the squabbles.\nHis wounds could reopen anytime.
Even my healing talent has its limits.
I must say, it's not very often we meet a\nsylvan from outside of Woodhaven.
Yes, I suppose it is rather unusual.\nSpeaking of which, do you know where\nthe other villagers are?
They're okay. The elder realized the Empire\nwas coming and brought us to safety.
Great! So where can we find them?
The forest refuge. You know the place.
Come with us, {player_name}.\nI'm sure everyone will want to meet the\nman who rescued Luca.
I've never seen so many sylvans\nin one place...
Nor I. Just look at all those ears!\nThere's a whole sea of them.
Er, well, I suppose they do have a\ncertain...flair.
What? Huh? Did I say something?\nUm...pay me no mind.
What were you thinking, taking on a\ndragon in battle?
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to put everyone\nthrough so much trouble.
You should be sorry. Houses can be rebuilt,\nbut lives are harder to piece back together.
I'll never do anything that stupid again.\nI swear it on my bow and in the name\nof Mother Nature.
I believe we owe you our gratitude,\ntravelers.
We only did what anyone would do.
And while I know it's not my place to tell\nyou what to do, Elder, the Empire's army\nis going to find this place soon.
We should devise a plan before that\nhappens.
Hmm... Then it's just as I feared.
But my people are not fighters,\nand we have nowhere else to run.
Eh, don't worry about that.\nWe'll keep ya safe.
All we gotta do is lure Emile away from his\ntroops and then ＂persuade＂ him to back off.
The first step is to hunt down the fiends\nthe Empire has loosed in the area.
